124 /* Trace type definitions. Note that these are mutually exclusive in a trace. This
125 means that any trace can be either error,warning,api,event or dbg */
126 #if (BTU_STACK_LITE_ENABLED == TRUE)
127 #define BTTRC_TYPE_ERROR 0x81
128 #define BTTRC_TYPE_WARNING 0x82
129 #define BTTRC_TYPE_API 0x84
130 #define BTTRC_TYPE_EVENT 0x88
131 #define BTTRC_TYPE_ACTION 0x90
132 #define BTTRC_TYPE_DBG 0xA0
133 #else
134 #define BTTRC_TYPE_ERROR 0x01 /* Traces for error situation */
135 #define BTTRC_TYPE_WARNING 0x02 /* Traces for warning situation */
136 #define BTTRC_TYPE_API 0x04 /* Traces for API */
137 #define BTTRC_TYPE_EVENT 0x08 /* Traces for EVENT */
138 #define BTTRC_TYPE_ACTION 0x10 /* Traces for Action functions */
139 #define BTTRC_TYPE_DBG 0x20 /* Traces for debugging purpose */
140 #endif
141 typedef UINT8 tBTTRC_TYPE;
142 
143 /* Masks to identify the stack that originated the trace */
144 #define BTTRC_TRACE_LITE 0x80 /* MM Lite stack */
145 #define BTTRC_TRACE_EMBD 0x40 /* Embedded host stack */
146 
147 /* Parameter datatypes used in Trace APIs */
148 #define BTTRC_PARAM_UINT8 1
149 #define BTTRC_PARAM_UINT16 2
150 #define BTTRC_PARAM_UINT32 3
151 typedef UINT8 tBTTRC_PARAM_TYPE;
152 
153 /* Special token definitions */
154 #define BTTRC_TOKEN_SM_STATE 0xFFFF /* Token indicating the State of a State m/c */

232 /* Enables or disables verbose trace information. */
233 #ifndef BT_TRACE_VERBOSE
234 #define BT_TRACE_VERBOSE FALSE
235 #endif
236 
237 /* Enables or disables all trace messages. */
238 #ifndef BT_USE_TRACES
239 #define BT_USE_TRACES TRUE
240 #endif
241 
242 /* Enables or disables protocol trace information. */
243 #ifndef BT_TRACE_PROTOCOL
244 #define BT_TRACE_PROTOCOL TRUE /* Android requires TRUE */
245 #endif
246 
247 /******************************************************************************
248 **
249 ** Trace Levels
250 **
251 ** The following values may be used for different levels:
252 ** BT_TRACE_LEVEL_NONE 0 * No trace messages to be generated
253 ** BT_TRACE_LEVEL_ERROR 1 * Error condition trace messages
254 ** BT_TRACE_LEVEL_WARNING 2 * Warning condition trace messages
255 ** BT_TRACE_LEVEL_API 3 * API traces
256 ** BT_TRACE_LEVEL_EVENT 4 * Debug messages for events
257 ** BT_TRACE_LEVEL_DEBUG 5 * Debug messages (general)
258 ******************************************************************************/
259
